The paper deals with graph optimization problems and kernelization, which are common topics in several sub-categories of arXiv CS. However, the focus on graph theory and optimization suggests that cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are the most likely categories. The use of kernelization techniques and the mention of bounded-degree graphs also suggest cs.CG (Computational Geometry) as a possible category. The paper also mentions local optimization and packing problems, which are relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), respectively.
